## **Appendix: De-Speculated Performance Projections**

| **Metric** | **SOTA (2025)** | **Goal (2028)** | **Hard Limit (Physics)** | **Notes** |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Unit Cost** | $0.02–0.05 | $0.005–0.01 | N/A | Gated by 300mm wafer adoption & Y_het_int > 0.85 |
| **Sensing Modalities** | 1 (Temp) | 2 (Temp + pH) | ~3–4 | Limited by area allocation & power-per-sensor |
| **Swarm Coordination** | ~100 units | ~1k units | ~10k units | Fundamental limit from viscous channel capacity |
| **Operational Lifetime** | 180 days | 2 years | Material degradation (~5 yrs est.) | In controlled fluid, continuous light |
| **In Vivo Applicability** | None | Toxicity studies complete | Requires new propulsion physics | H₂O₂ toxicity is a fundamental barrier for current design |

---

## **Final Directive**

This field's credibility depends on **declaring what is impossible as clearly as what is achieved.** The next phase of work must prioritize **reliability, measurable yield, and contained demonstrations** over speculative applications. Progress will be measured by the closure of specific, declared Engineering Readiness Levels (ERLs), not by narrative.

